Sentencing proceeded.  Statements by the State, defense and defendant. 
As to Count 1:  The Court sentenced the defendant to a MAXIMUM TERM OF IMPRISONMENT of  9 YEARS with 220 days credit CONCURRENT to Count 2; the INITIAL TERM OF CONFINEMENT in the Wisconsin State Prison System is 4.5 YEARS; the MAXIMUM TERM OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION is 4.5 YEARS.
As to Count 2:  The Court sentenced the defendant to a MAXIMUM TERM OF IMPRISONMENT of  9 YEARS CONCURRENT  to Count 3; the INITIAL TERM OF CONFINEMENT in the Wisconsin State Prison System is 4.5 YEARS; the MAXIMUM TERM OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION is 4.5 YEARS.
As to Count 3:  The Court sentenced the defendant to a MAXIMUM TERM OF IMPRISONMENT of  9 YEARS CONCURRENT  to Count 4; the INITIAL TERM OF CONFINEMENT in the Wisconsin State Prison System is 4.5 YEARS; the MAXIMUM TERM OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION is 4.5 YEARS.
As to Count 4:  The Court sentenced the defendant to a MAXIMUM TERM OF IMPRISONMENT of  9 YEARS; the INITIAL TERM OF CONFINEMENT in the Wisconsin State Prison System is 4.5 YEARS; the MAXIMUM TERM OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION is 4.5 YEARS.
These sentences are CONSECUTIVE to any other sentence.

Defendant Lori L Wilbur in court with attorney Douglas Michael Bihler.  Defendant Lori L Wilbur in custody.  Ron Dague appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Deputy court clerk:  vk  As to all Counts:  Defendant was advised of constitutional rights and maximum penalties, waived all rights, plead GUILTY and was examined as to the plea.  Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights, Addendum, elements and jury instructions, received and filed.  Parties stipulate to the complaint as a factual basis for the plea.  Defendant further advised that if she is not a US citizen deportation is possible.  Court found defendant guilty as charged in the Information and ordered entry of Judgment of Conviction.  
Court advised defendant that as a convicted felon she may never possess a firearm.  Court advised defendant that his voting rights are suspended, and may not vote in any election until her civil rights are restored.
Defendant is ordered to provide a DNA sample.  
Court REMANDS the defendant.  Case is adjourned for sentencing in Branch 19.  Sentencing hearing scheduled for September 21, 2015 at 08:30 am.
